  "prompt": "When and how did Gautama Buddha die?",
  "response": "Gautama Buddha, the founder of Buddhism, is traditionally believed to have died around 483 BCE. His death is known as the Parinirvana, which refers to the final passing away of someone who has attained Nirvana.\n\nAccording to Buddhist texts, Buddha died at the age of 80 in a place called Kushinagar, which is located in present-day Uttar Pradesh, India. The circumstances of his death are described in various texts, including the Mahaparinibbana Sutta of the Pali Canon.\n\nBuddha fell ill after consuming a meal offered to him by a blacksmith named Cunda. Despite the illness, he was said to have shown a remarkable equanimity and calm in the face of death. Before passing away, he delivered his final teachings to his disciples, emphasizing the impermanence of life and encouraging them to continue following his path of practice. \n\nHe ultimately passed away in a peaceful state, lying between two trees, and his last words were reportedly a reminder to his followers to be diligent in their practice and to cultivate their own understanding. After his death, his remains were cremated, and various monuments called stupas were built to honor his memory.",
